@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

  This door has three modes, see @{"System Options" link SystemOptions}

  Pesudo code:

  if SystemOption is "LOGIN_CHECK" then
  begin

    "You still have these tagged files from your last call"
    (and list tagged files)
    "Do you want to keep them [Y/N]"

    if "Nope" then clear all tags, continue otherwise

    exit

  else

    ran door without options ?

    begin

      repeat

        Display tagged files

        ask whether to clear all or add/remove single tags.

      until user quits door

      exit

    else

      perform required options (Tag, Clear, List, Help)

      exit

    end
  end

@EndNode


@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    This door is installed as part of the default HBBS setup

    Create a new directory "HBBS:Doors/User/CheckTags"
    Copy "CheckTags.HBBS" to it

    Add options to HBBS:Commands/System like this:

    CheckTags_Type_1=HBBS
    CheckTags_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/User/CheckTags/CheckTags.HBBS {N} {O}
    CheckTags_Param_1=LOGIN_CHECK

    Add options to HBBS:Commands/All_Levels like this:

    A_Type_1=HBBS
    A_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/User/CheckTags/CheckTags.HBBS {N} {O}

@EndNode

@Node SystemOptions "SystemOptions"

  System Options
  ==============

    LOGIN_CHECK - enables login check mode.
    NOUSER      - enables non prompting mode.

    Call with no system options and no paramaters to enable
    interactive mode

    If called with no system options but with paramaters then
    the paramaters will be checked and worked upon.

@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    Command line options only used in INTERACTIVE or NON interactive mode.


    <list of files to be tagged with spaces seperating names>

    or

    A <filename> - calls TAG_FILE with list of files
    C <filename> - clears filename from listof tagged files
    *            - clears list of tagged files.
    L            - lists tagged files
    ?            - displays help.

@EndNode

@Node ScreensDisplayed "Screens Displayed"

  Screens Displayed
  =================

    None

  Special Screens Displayed
  =========================

    Banner_TOP - When listing currently tagged files
    Banner_BOT - As above

@EndNode

@Node DoorsCalled "Doors Called"

  Doors Called
  ============

    System doors:

    TAG_FILE C=<confnum>,N=<filename> ...  (e.g. C=2,N=Moo.lha C=2,N=COW.DMS)


@EndNode

